<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-13T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.48/134a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-13T15:00:00-05:00">January
                                    13, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>32. The American press has recently carried reports from France to the
                            effect that in view of serious food shortages in occupied France food
                            supplies are being sent from unoccupied territory, particularly to
                            Paris.</p>
                        <p>Please telegraph any information you may be able to obtain concerning the
                            authenticity of such reports.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>